1. Summon focused fire pet (unfocused might work too) <br>
2. Summon plate, dont give the bracers however <br>
3. Summon daggar of symbols x 2 <br>
4. summon focus items.. if two can be equiped give him two. (e.g. two bracers, two baubles, and two rings) <br>
5. elemental defender for backslot <br>
6. bo2, expidence, make damn sure firepet has his DS up. <br>
7. set up your pet far away from adds.. i actally set up on the AC island, pulled with lv8 bolt and ran like hell.. with sow you dont need to get the intial distance tho..  they will outrun you normally, not sure about jboots however. <br>
8. once he nears your pet, sic the pet on him and MED! watch your pets health, and near 60% throw a renew summoning on him.. if your at fm you can do it earlier <br>
9. med again and watch the mobs health and your pets.. i just have the sf clicked and have a hotkey for /pet report health <br>
10. heal your pet as needed with the new 44 heal.. i usally heal around 40%, these things hit weak so your not in THAT much danger of 3-4 good attack rounds whiping your pet out.. but dont let your pet fall too low on hp. <br>
11. med back up to fm and heal or let the pet regen to FH. sometimes i end with 98% mana.. but pets at 25% hp <br>
<br>
overall: soloable, fun to kill a giant, but the fights are long because of their high hp. <br>
1-2% xp per kill, gems sell for good money to vendors. <br>
<br>
The only problems i ever had with these, was when one caught up to me while pulling to ac island, and when i tried one on the sf island. They run and you have to burn mana nuking them.<br>
<br>
edit: currently at 45 im no longer aiming for SF's but going for AC camp first, and gornit second.  all 3 (sf\ac [and the cyclopse ph's]\gornit) give me xp, gornit gives good cash, and ac gives me a shot at getting my jboots <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nimmamen>Nimmamen</A> at: 1/25/03 4:00:21 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aequi>aequi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#333333>(2/17/03 12:04:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=174.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Seafurys at 44?</span><hr size=1> Keep coming back to this post to see if anyone had replied to it, added information or made corrections - Are seafuries too difficult at 44 if you don't have access to things like SOW or jboots? or just not a good spot?<br>
